obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32468)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32468&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Payment and Settlement`
  line `Systems Act, 2007.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and`
  line `any reference to the commencement in any such provision of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the commencement of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 12th August, 2008, vide notification No. S.O. 2032(E), dated 12th August, 2008, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32469)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32469&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "bank" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) a bank included in the Second Schedule to the Reserve Bank of India Act,`
  line `1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(ii) a post office savings bank;`
  line
  line `(iii) a banking company as defined in clause (c) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act,`
  line `1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(iv) a co-operative bank as defined in clause (cci) of section 5, as inserted by section 56 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949); and`
  line
  line `(v) such other bank as the Reserve Bank may, by notification, specify for the purposes of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(b)"derivative" means an instrument, to be settled at a future date, whose value is derived from`
  line `change in interest rate, foreign exchange rate, credit rating or credit index, price of securities (also`
  line `called "underlying"), or any other underlying or a combination of more than one of them and includes`
  line `interest rate swaps, forward rate agreements, foreign currency swaps, foreign currency rupee swaps,`
  line `foreign currency options, foreign currency rupee options or any other instrument, as may be specified`
  line `by the Reserve Bank from time to time;`
  line
  line `(c) "electronic funds transfer" means any transfer of funds which is initiated by a person by way`
  line `of instruction, authorisation or order to a bank to debit or credit an account maintained with that bank`
  line `through electronic means and includes point of sale transfers, automated teller machine transactions,`
  line `direct deposits or withdrawal of funds, transfers initiated by telephone, internet and card payment;`
  line
  line `(d) "gross settlement system" means a payment system in which each settlement of funds or`
  line `securities occurs on the basis of separate or individual instructions;`
  line
  line `^1[(da) "issuer" means a person who issues a legal entity identifier or such other unique`
  line `identification (by whatever name called), as may be specified by the Reserve Bank from time to time;`
  line
  line `(db) "legal entity identifier" means a unique identity code assigned to a person by an issuer for`
  line `the purpose of identifying that person in such derivatives or financial transactions, as may be`
  line `specified by the Reserve Bank from time to time;]`
  line
  line `(e) "netting" means the determination by the system provider of the amount of money or`
  line `securities, due or payable or deliverable, as a result of setting off or adjusting, the payment`
  line `obligations or delivery obligations among the system participants, including the claims and`
  line `obligations arising out of the termination by the system provider, on the insolvency or dissolution or`
  line `winding up of any system participant or such other circumstances as the system provider may specify`
  line `in its rules or regulations or bye-laws (by whatever name called), of the transactions admitted for`
  line `settlement at a future date so that only a net claim be demanded or a net obligation be owned;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "payment instruction" means any instrument, authorisation or order in any form, including`
  line `electronic means, to effect a payment,--`
  line
  line `(i) by a person to a system participant; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by a system participant to another system participant;`
  line
  line `(h) "payment obligation" means an indebtedness that is owned by one system participant to`
  line `another system participant as a result of clearing or settlement of one or more payment instructions`
  line `relating to funds, securities or foreign exchange or derivatives or other transactions;`
  line
  line `(i) "payment system" means a system that enables payment to be effected between a payer and a`
  line `beneficiary, involving clearing, payment or settlement service or all of them, but does not include a`
  line `stock exchange.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "payment system" includes the systems enabling`
  line `credit card operations, debit card operations, smart card operations, money transfer operations or`
  line `similar operations;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "regulation" means a regulation made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India, constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(m) "securities" means the Government securities as defined in the Public Debt Act,`
  line `1944 (18 of 1944) or such other securities as may be notified by the Central Government from time to`
  line `time under that Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "settlement" means settlement of payment instructions and includes the settlement of`
  line `securities, foreign exchange or derivatives or other transactions which involve payment obligations;`
  line
  line `(o) "systemic risk" means the risk arising from--`
  line
  line `(i) the inability of a system participant to meet his payment obligations under the payment`
  line `system as and when they become due; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any disruption in the system,`
  line
  line `which may cause other participants to fail to meet their obligations when due and is likely to have an`
  line `impact on the stability of the system:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any doubt or difference arises as to whether a particular risk is likely to have an`
  line `impact on the stability of the system, the decision of the Reserve Bank shall be final;`
  line
  line `(p) "system participant" means a bank or any other person participating in a payment system and`
  line `includes the system provider;`
  line
  line `(q) "system provider" means a person who operates an authorised payment system;`
  line
  line `^3[(r) "trade repository" means a person who is engaged in the business of collecting, collating,`
  line `storing, maintaining, processing or disseminating electronic records or data relating to such`
  line `derivatives or financial transactions, as may be specified by the Reserve Bank from time to time.]`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used, but not defined in this Act and defined in the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) or the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32470)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Designated authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32470&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Designated authority.--(1) The Reserve Bank shall be the designated authority for the regulation`
  line `and supervision of payment systems under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank shall exercise the powers, perform the functions and discharge the duties`
  line `conferred on it under this Act through a Board to be known as the "Payments Regulatory Board".`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Governor of the Reserve Bank-Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Deputy Governor of the Reserve Bank in-charge of the Payment and Settlement Systems-Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) one officer of the Reserve Bank to be nominated by the Central Board of the Reserve Bank-Member, ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(d) three persons to be nominated by the Central Government-Members.`
  line
  line `(4) The powers and functions of the Board referred to in sub-section (2), the time and venue of its`
  line `meetings, the procedures to be followed in such meetings (including the quorum at such meetings) and`
  line `other matters incidental thereto shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Finance Act 2017, s. 152, for the following :--`
  line
  line `"CHAPTER II`
  line
  line `DESIGNATED AUTHORITY AND ITS COMMITTEE`
  line
  line `3. Designated authority and its Committee.--(1) The Reserve Bank shall be the designated authority for the regulation`
  line `and supervision of payment systems under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, for the purposes of exercising the powers and performing the functions and discharging the`
  line `duties conferred on it by or under this Act, by regulation, constitute a committee of its Central Board to be known as the Board`
  line `for Regulation and Supervision of Payment and Settlement Systems.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board constituted under sub-section (2) shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Governor, Reserve Bank, who shall be the Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) Deputy Governors, Reserve Bank, out of whom the Deputy Governor who is in-charge of the Payment and`
  line `Settlement Systems, shall be the Vice-Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) Not exceeding three Directors from the Central Board of the Reserve Bank of India to be nominated by the`
  line `Governor, Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) The powers and functions of the Board constituted under sub-section (2), the time and venue of its meetings, the`
  line `procedure to be followed in such meetings, (including the quorum at such meetings) and other matters incidental thereto shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board for Regulation and Supervision of Payment and Settlement Systems constituted under clause (i) of subsection (2) of section 58 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) shall be deemed to be the Board constituted under`
  line `this section and continue accordingly until the Board is reconstituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act and shall be`
  line `governed by the rules and regulations made under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 in so far as they are not inconsistent with`
  line `the provisions of this Act."`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32471)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Payment system not to operate without authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32471&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, other than the Reserve`
  line `Bank, shall commence or operate a payment system except under and in accordance with an authorisation`
  line `issued by the Reserve Bank under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the continued operation of an existing payment system on commencement of this Act for a`
  line `period not exceeding six months from such commencement, unless within such period, the operator`
  line `of such payment system obtains an authorisation under this Act or the application for authorisation`
  line `made under section 7 of this Act is refused by the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) any person acting as the duly appointed agent of another person to whom the payment is due;`
  line
  line `(c) a company accepting payments either from its holding company or any of its subsidiary`
  line `companies or from any other company which is also a subsidiary of the same holding company;`
  line
  line `(d) any other person whom the Reserve Bank may, after considering the interests of monetary`
  line `policy or efficient operation of payment systems, the size of any payment system or for any other`
  line `reason, by notification, exempt from the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, under sub-section (1) of this section, authorise a company or corporation`
  line `to operate or regulate the existing clearing houses or new clearing houses of banks in order to have a`
  line `common retail clearing house system for the banks throughout the country:`
  line
  line `Provided, however, that not less than fifty-one per cent. of the equity of such company or corporation`
  line `shall be held by public sector banks.`
  line
  line `"Explanation".--For the purposes of this clause, "public sector banks" shall include a "corresponding`
  line `new bank", "State Bank of India" and "subsidiary bank" as defined in section 5 of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32472)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Application for authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32472&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desirous of commencing or carrying on a`
  line `payment system may apply to the Reserve Bank for an authorisation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and in such manner and shall be`
  line `accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32473)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Inquiry by the Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32473&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `After the receipt of an application under section 5, and before an`
  line `authorisation is issued under this Act, the Reserve Bank may make such inquiries as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the purpose of satisfying itself about the genuineness of the particulars furnished by the`
  line `applicant, his capacity to operate the payment system, the credentials of the participants or for any other`
  line `reason and when such an inquiry is conducted by any person authorised by it in this behalf, it may require`
  line `a report from such person in respect of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32474)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Issue or refusal of authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32474&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank may, if satisfied, after any inquiry`
  line `under section 6 or otherwise, that the application is complete in all respects and that it conforms to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the regulations issue an authorisation for operating the payment system under`
  line `this Act having regard to the following considerations, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the need for the proposed payment system or the services proposed to be undertaken by it;`
  line
  line `(ii) the technical standards or the design of the proposed payment system;`
  line
  line `(iii) the terms and conditions of operation of the proposed payment system including any security`
  line procedure;
  line
  line `(iv) the manner in which transfer of funds may be effected within the payment system;`
  line
  line `(v) the procedure for netting of payment instructions effecting the payment obligations under the`
  line `payment system;`
  line
  line `(vi) the financial status, experience of management and integrity of the applicant;`
  line
  line `(vii) interests of consumers, including the terms and conditions governing their relationship with`
  line `payment system providers;`
  line
  line `(viii) monetary and credit policies; and`
  line
  line `(ix) such other factors as may be considered relevant by the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) An authorisation issued under sub-section (1) shall be in such form as may be prescribed and`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) state the date on which it takes effect;`
  line
  line `(b) state the conditions subject to which the authorisation shall be in force;`
  line
  line `(c) indicate the payment of fees, if any, to be paid for the authorisation to be in force;`
  line
  line `(d) if it considers necessary, require the applicant to furnish such security for the proper conduct`
  line `of the payment system under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) continue to be in force till the authorisation is revoked.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Reserve Bank considers that the application for authorisation should be refused, it shall`
  line `give the applicant a written notice to that effect stating the reasons for the refusal:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such application shall be refused unless the applicant is given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) Every application for authorisation shall be processed by the Reserve Bank as soon as possible`
  line `and an endeavour shall be made to dispose of such application within six months from the date of filing of`
  line `such application.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32475)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Revocation of authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32475&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a system provider,--`
  line
  line `(i) contravenes any provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(ii) does not comply with the regulations, or`
  line
  line `(iii) fails to comply with the orders or directions issued by the designated authority, or`
  line
  line `(iv) operates the payment system contrary to the conditions subject to which the authorisation was`
  line issued,
  line
  line `the Reserve Bank may, by order, revoke the authorisation given to such system provider under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of revocation under sub-section (1) shall be made--`
  line
  line `(i) except after giving the system provider a reasonable opportunity of being heard; and`
  line
  line `(ii) without prejudice to the direction of the Reserve Bank to the system provider that the`
  line `operation of the payment system shall not be carried out till the order of revocation is issued.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to a case where the Reserve Bank considers it`
  line `necessary to revoke the authorisation given to a payment system in the interest of the monetary policy of`
  line `the country or for any other reasons to be specified by it in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) The order of revocation issued under sub-section (1) shall include necessary provisions to protect`
  line `and safeguard the interests of persons affected by such order of revocation.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a system provider becomes insolvent or dissolved or wound up, such system provider shall`
  line `inform that fact to the Reserve Bank and thereupon the Reserve Bank shall take such steps as deemed`
  line `necessary to revoke the authorisation issued to such system provider to operate the payment system.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32476)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appeal to the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32476&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any applicant for an authorisation whose application`
  line `for the operation of the payment system is refused under sub-section (3) of section 7 or a system provider`
  line `who is aggrieved by an order of revocation under section 8 may, within thirty days from the date on`
  line `which the order is communicated to him, appeal to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall endeavour to dispose of an appeal under sub-section (1) within a`
  line `period of three months.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Central Government on the appeal under sub-section (1) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32477)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to determine standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32477&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank may, from time to time, prescribe--`
  line
  line `(a) the format of payment instructions and the size and shape of such instructions;`
  line
  line `(b) the timings to be maintained by payment systems;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of transfer of funds within the payment system, either through paper, electronic`
  line `means or in any other manner, between banks or between banks and other system participants;`
  line
  line `(d) such other standards to be complied with the payment systems generally;`
  line
  line `(e) the criteria for membership of payment systems including continuation, termination and`
  line `rejection of membership;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions subject to which the system participants shall participate in such fund transfers`
  line `and the rights and obligations of the system participants in such funds.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank may, from time to time,`
  line `issue such guidelines, as it may consider necessary for the proper and efficient management of the`
  line `payment systems generally or with reference to any particular payment system.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (50219)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Bank, etc., not to impose charge for using electronic modes of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 204 (w.e.f. 1-11-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=50219&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Bank, etc., not to impose charge for using electronic modes of payment.--Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, no bank or system provider shall impose, whether directly or indirectly,`
  line `any charge upon a person making or receiving a payment by using the electronic modes of payment`
  line `prescribed under section 269SU of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32478)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Notice of change in the payment system.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32478&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No system provider shall cause any change in the`
  line `system which would affect the structure or the operation of the payment system without--`
  line
  line `(a) the prior approval of the Reserve Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) giving notice of not less than thirty days to the system participants after the approval of the`
  line `Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the interest of monetary policy of the country or in public interest, the Reserve`
  line `Bank may permit the system provider to make any changes in a payment system without giving`
  line `notice to the system participants under clause (b) or requiring the system provider to give notice for a`
  line `period longer than thirty days.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Reserve Bank has any objection, to the proposed change for any reason, it shall`
  line `communicate such objection to the systems provider within two weeks of receipt of the intimation of the`
  line `proposed changes from the system provider.`
  line
  line `(3) The system provider shall, within a period of two weeks of the receipt of the objections from the`
  line `Reserve Bank forward his comments to the Reserve Bank and the proposed changes may be effected only`
  line `after the receipt of approval from the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32479)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to call for returns, documents or other information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32479&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank may call for`
  line `from any system provider such returns or documents as it may require or other information in regard to`
  line `the operation of his payment system at such intervals, in such form and in such manner, as the Reserve`
  line `Bank may require from time to time or as may be prescribed and such order shall be complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32480)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Access to information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32480&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank shall have right to access any information relating to`
  line `the operation of any payment system and system provider and all the system participants shall provide`
  line `access to such information to the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32481)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to enter and inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32481&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any officer of the Reserve Bank duly authorised by it in writing in`
  line `this behalf, may for ensuring compliance with the provisions of this Act or any regulations, enter any`
  line `premises where a payment system is being operated and may inspect any equipment, including any`
  line `computer system or other documents situated at such premises and call upon any employee of such`
  line `system provider or participant thereof or any other person working in such premises to furnish such`
  line `information or documents as may be required by such officer`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32482)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Information, etc., to be confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32482&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), any`
  line `document or information obtained by the Reserve Bank under sections 12 to 14 (both inclusive) shall be`
  line `kept confidential.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank may disclose any`
  line `document or information obtained by it under sections 12 to 14 (both inclusive) to any person to whom`
  line `the disclosure of such document or information is considered necessary for protecting the integrity,`
  line `effectiveness or security of the payment system, or in the interest of banking or monetary policy or the`
  line `operation of the payment systems generally or in the public interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32483)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to carry out audit and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32483&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank may, for the purpose of carrying`
  line `out its functions under this Act, conduct or get conducted audits and inspections of a payment system or`
  line `participants thereof and it shall be the duty of the system provider and the system participants to assist the`
  line `Reserve Bank to carry out such audit or inspection, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32484)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32484&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where the Reserve Bank is of the opinion that,--`
  line
  line `(a) a payment system or a system participant is engaging in, or is about to engage in, any act,`
  line `omission or course of conduct that results, or is likely to result, in systemic risk being inadequately`
  line `controlled; or`
  line
  line `(b) any action under clause (a) is likely to affect the payment system, the monetary policy or the`
  line `credit policy of the country,`
  line
  line `the Reserve Bank may issue directions in writing to such payment system or system participant requiring`
  line `it, within such time as the Reserve Bank may specify--`
  line
  line `(i) to cease and desist from engaging in the act, omission or course of conduct or to ensure the`
  line `system participants to cease and desist from the act, omission or course of conduct; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to perform such acts as may be necessary, in the opinion of the Reserve Bank, to remedy the`
  line situation.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32485)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to give directions generally.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32485&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `the foregoing, the Reserve Bank may, if it is satisfied that for the purpose of enabling it to regulate the`
  line `payment systems or in the interest of management or operation of any of the payment systems or in public`
  line `interest, it is necessary so to do, lay down policies relating to the regulation of payment systems including`
  line `electronic, non-electronic, domestic and international payment systems affecting domestic transactions`
  line `and give such directions in writing as it may consider necessary to system providers or the system`
  line `participants or any other person either generally or to any such agency and in particular, pertaining to the`
  line `conduct of business relating to payment systems.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32486)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Directions of Reserve Bank to be complied with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32486&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every person to whom a direction has been`
  line `issued by the Reserve Bank under this Act shall comply with such direction without any delay and a`
  line `report of compliance shall be furnished to the Reserve Bank within the time allowed by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32487)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `System provider to act in accordance with the Act, regulations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32487&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every system provider`
  line `shall operate the payment system in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the regulations, the`
  line `contract governing the relationship among the system participants, the rules and regulations which deal`
  line `with the operation of the payment system and the conditions subject to which the authorisation is issued,`
  line `and the directions given by the Reserve Bank from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32488)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Duties of a system provider.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32488&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every system provider shall disclose to the existing or`
  line `potential system participants, the terms and conditions including the charges and the limitations of`
  line `liability under the payment system, supply them with copies of the rules and regulations governing the`
  line `operation of the payment system, netting arrangements and other relevant documents.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every system provider to maintain the standards determined under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32489)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Duty to keep documents in the payment system confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32489&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A system provider shall not`
  line `disclose to any other person the existence or contents of any document or part thereof or other`
  line `information given to him by a system participant, except where such disclosure is required under the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the disclosure is made with the express or implied consent of the system`
  line `participant concerned or where such disclosure is in obedience to the orders passed by a court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction or a statutory authority in exercise of the powers conferred by a statute.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Bankers’ Book Evidence Act, 1891(18 of 1991) shall apply in relation to the`
  line `information or documents or other books in whatever form maintained by the system provider.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32490)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Settlement and netting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32490&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The payment obligations and settlement instructions among the`
  line `system participants shall be determined in accordance with the gross or netting procedure, as the case may be, approved by the Reserve Bank while issuing authorisation to a payment system ^1[under section 7, or,`
  line `such gross or netting procedure as may be approved by it under any other provisions of this Act].`
  line
  line `(2) Where the rules providing for the operation of a payment system indicates a procedure for the`
  line `distribution of losses between the system participants and the payment system, such procedure shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) A settlement effected under such procedure shall be final and irrevocable.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) Where, by an order of a court, Tribunal or authority--`
  line
  line `(a) a system participant is declared as insolvent or is dissolved or wound up; or`
  line
  line `(b) a liquidator or receiver or assignee (by whatever name called), whether provisional or otherwise, is appointed in a proceeding relating to insolvency or dissolution or winding up of a system participant,`
  line
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in the Banking Regulation Act,1949 (10 of 1949) or the Companies Act,1956 (1 of 1956) or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) ^3[or the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016] or any other law for the time being in force, such order shall not affect any settlement that has become final and irrevocable prior to such order or immediately thereafter, and the right of the system provider to appropriate any collaterals contributed by the system participants towards its settlement or other obligations in accordance with the rules, regulations or bye-laws relating to such system provider.]`
  line
  line `^4[(5) Where an order referred to in sub-section (4) is made with respect to a central counter party,`
  line `then, notwithstanding such order or anything contained in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)`
  line `or the Companies Act,1956 (1 of 1956) or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2015) ^3[or the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016] or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, the payment obligations and settlement instructions between the central counter party`
  line `and the system participants including those arising from transactions admitted for settlement at a future`
  line `date, shall be determined forthwith by such central counter party in accordance with the gross or netting`
  line `procedure, as the case may be, approved by the Reserve Bank, while issuing authorisation or under any`
  line `other provisions of this Act, and such determination shall be final and irrevocable.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) or the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) ^3[or the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016] or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the liquidator or receiver or assignee (by whatever name called) of the central counter`
  line `party, whether appointed as provisional or otherwise, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) not re-open any determination that has become final and irrevocable;`
  line
  line `(b) after appropriating in accordance with the rules, regulations or bye-laws of the central counter`
  line `party, the collaterals provided by the system participants towards their settlement or other obligations,`
  line `return the collaterals held in excess to the system participants concerned.]`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation 1].--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the settlement, whether gross`
  line `or net, referred to in this section is final and irrevocable as soon as the money, securities, foreign`
  line `exchange or derivatives or other transactions payable as a result of such settlement is determined, whether`
  line `or not such money, securities or foreign exchange or derivatives or other transactions is actually paid.`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation 2].--For the purposes of this section, the expression "central counter party" means a`
  line `system provider who by way of novation interposes between system participants in the transactions`
  line `admitted for settlement, thereby becoming the buyer to every seller and the seller to every buyer, for the`
  line `purpose of effecting settlement of their transactions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2015, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 253 and the Ninth Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line
  line `5. Existing Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line
  line `6.The Explanation 2 ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (32491)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 25
  title `Protection of funds collected from customers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32491&sectionno=23A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A.--Protection of funds collected from customers. (1) The Reserve Bank may, in public`
  line `interest or in the interest of the customers of designated payment systems or to prevent the affairs of such`
  line `designated payment system from being conducted in a manner prejudicial to the interests of its customers,`
  line `require system provider of such payment system to--`
  line
  line `(a) deposit and keep deposited in a separate account or accounts held in a scheduled commercial`
  line `bank; or`
  line
  line `(b) maintain liquid assets in such manner and form as it may specify from time to time,`
  line
  line `of an amount equal to such percentage of the amounts collected by the system provider of designated`
  line `payment system from its customers and remaining outstanding, as may be specified by the Reserve Bank`
  line `from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Reserve Bank may specify different percentages and the manner and forms for`
  line `different categories of designated payment systems.`
  line
  line `(2) The balance held in the account or accounts, referred to in sub-section (1), shall not be utilised for`
  line `any purpose other than for discharging the liabilities arising on account of the usage of the payment`
  line `service by the customers or for repaying to the customers or for such other purpose as may be specified`
  line `by the Reserve Bank from time to time.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), or the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) ^2[or the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016] or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the persons entitled to receive payment under sub-section (2) shall have a first and`
  line `paramount charge on the balance held in that account and the liquidator or receiver or assignee (by`
  line `whatever name called) of the system provider of the designated payment system or the scheduled`
  line `commercial bank concerned, whether appointed as provisional or otherwise, shall not utilise the said`
  line `balances for any other purposes until all such persons are paid in full or adequate provision is made`
  line therefor.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expressions--`
  line
  line `(a) "designated payment system" shall mean a payment system or a class of payment system, as`
  line `may be specified by the Reserve Bank from time to time, engaged in collection of funds from their`
  line `customers for rendering payment service;`
  line
  line `(b) "scheduled commercial bank" shall mean a "banking company", "corresponding new bank",`
  line `"State Bank of India" and "subsidiary bank" as defined in section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act,`
  line `1949 (10 of 1949) and included in the Second Schedule to the Reserve Bank of India Act,`
  line `1934 (2 of 1934).]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2015, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 253 and the Ninth Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32492)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Settlement of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32492&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The system provider shall make provision in its rules or regulations`
  line `for creation of panel consisting of not less than three system participants other than the system`
  line `participants who are parties to the dispute to decide the disputes between system participants in respect of`
  line `any matter connected with the operation of the payment system.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any dispute in respect of any matter connected with the operation of the payment system`
  line `arises between two or more system participants, the system provider shall refer the dispute to the panel`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where any dispute arises between any system participant and the system provider or between`
  line `system providers or where any of the system participants is not satisfied with the decision of the panel`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), the dispute shall be referred to the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) The dispute referred to the Reserve Bank for adjudication under sub-section (3) shall be disposed`
  line `of by an officer of the Reserve Bank generally or specially authorised in this behalf and the decision of`
  line `the Reserve Bank shall be final and binding.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a dispute arises between the Reserve Bank, while acting in its capacity as system provider`
  line `or as system participant, and another system provider or system participant, the matter shall be referred to`
  line `the Central Government which may authorise an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary for`
  line `settlement of the dispute and the decision of such officer shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32493)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Dishonour of electronic funds transfer for insufficiency, etc., of funds in the account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32493&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where an electronic funds transfer initiated by a person from an account maintained by him cannot be`
  line `executed on the ground that the amount of money standing to the credit of that account is insufficient to`
  line `honour the transfer instruction or that it exceeds the amount arranged to be paid from that account by an`
  line `agreement made with a bank, such person shall be deemed to have committed an offence and shall,`
  line `without prejudice to any other provisions of this Act, be punished with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to twice the amount of the electronic funds`
  line `transfer, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the electronic funds transfer was initiated for payment of any amount of money to another`
  line `person for the discharge, in whole or in part, of any debt or other liability;`
  line
  line `(b) the electronic funds transfer was initiated in accordance with the relevant procedural`
  line `guidelines issued by the system provider;`
  line
  line `(c) the beneficiary makes a demand for the payment of the said amount of money by giving a`
  line `notice in writing to the person initiating the electronic funds transfer within thirty days of the receipt`
  line `of information by him from the bank concerned regarding the dishonour of the electronic funds`
  line `transfer; and`
  line
  line `(d) the person initiating the electronic funds transfer fails to make the payment of the said money`
  line `to the beneficiary within fifteen days of the receipt of the said notice.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that the electronic funds transfer was initiated`
  line `for the discharge, in whole or in part, of any debt or other liability.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall not be a defence in a prosecution for an offence under sub-section (1) that the person, who`
  line `initiated the electronic funds transfer through an instruction, authorisation, order or agreement, did not`
  line `have reason to believe at the time of such instruction, authorisation, order or agreement that the credit of`
  line `his account is insufficient to effect the electronic funds transfer.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court shall, in respect of every proceeding under this section, on production of a`
  line `communication from the bank denoting the dishonour of electronic funds transfer, presume the fact of`
  line `dishonour of such electronic funds transfer, unless and until such fact is disproved.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of Chapter XVII of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881) shall apply`
  line `to the dishonour of electronic funds transfer to the extent the circumstances admit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "debt or other liability" means a legally enforceable`
  line `debt or other liability, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32494)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32494&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person contravenes the provisions of section 4 or fails to comply with the`
  line `terms and conditions subject to which the authorisation has been issued under section 7, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one month but which may extend to`
  line `ten years or with fine which may extend to one crore rupees or with both and with a further fine which`
  line `may extend to one lakh rupees for every day, after the first during which the contravention or failure to`
  line `comply continues.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever in any application for authorisation or in any return or other document or on any`
  line `information required to be furnished by or under, or for the purpose of, any provision of this Act, wilfully`
  line `makes a statement which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false or wilfully omits to`
  line `make a material statement, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees and which may extend to`
  line `fifty lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person fails to produce any statement, information, returns or other documents, or to furnish`
  line `any statement, information, returns or other documents, which under section 12 or under section 13, it is`
  line `his duty to furnish or to answer any question relating to the operation of a payment system which is`
  line `required by an officer making inspection under section 14, he shall be ^1ic956liable to penalty as may be`
  line `imposed in accordance with the provisions of section 30].`
  line
  line `(4) If any person discloses any information, the disclosure of which is prohibited under section 22, he`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five lakh rupees or an amount equal to twice the amount of the damages incurred by the act`
  line `of such disclosure, whichever is higher or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a direction issued under this Act is not complied with within the period stipulated by the`
  line `Reserve Bank or where no such period is stipulated, within a reasonable time or where the penalty`
  line `imposed by the Reserve Bank under section 30 is not paid within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the order, the system provider or the system participant which has failed to comply with the direction or`
  line `to pay the penalty shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one`
  line `month but which may extend to ten years, or with fine which may extend to one crore rupees or with both`
  line `and where the failure to comply with the direction continues, with further fine which may extend to one`
  line `lakh rupees for every day, after the first during which the contravention continues.`
  line
  line `(6) If any provision of this Act is contravened, or if any default is made in complying with any other requirement of this Act, or of any regulation, order or direction made or given or condition imposed thereunder and in respect of which no penalty has been specified, then, the person guilty of such contravention or default, as the case may be, shall be ^1[liable to penalty as may be imposed in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of section 30].`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32495)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32495&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person committing a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any regulation, direction or order made thereunder is a company, every person`
  line `who, at the time of the contravention, was in-charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the`
  line `conduct of business of the company, as well as the company, shall be guilty of the contravention and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to punishment`
  line `if he proves that the contravention took place without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence`
  line `to prevent such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any regulation, direction or order made thereunder has been committed by a`
  line `company and it is proved that the contravention has taken place with the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company,`
  line `such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of the contravention`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32496)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32496&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act except upon a complaint in writing made by an officer of the Reserve Bank generally or specially`
  line `authorised by it in writing in this behalf, and no court, lower than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall try any such offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may take cognizance of an offence punishable under section 25 upon a`
  line `complaint in writing made by the person aggrieved by the dishonour of the electronic funds transfer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a`
  line `Magistrate may dispense with the personal attendance of the officer of the Reserve Bank filing the`
  line `complaint, but the Magistrate may, in his discretion, at any stage of the proceedings, direct the personal`
  line `attendance of the complainant.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32497)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Application of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32497&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `A court imposing any fine under this Act may direct that the whole or any`
  line `part thereof shall be applied in, or towards payment of, the costs of the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32498)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32498&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `30. Power of Reserve Bank to impose ^1[penalties].--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 26, if a contravention or default of the nature referred to in sub-section (2) ^2[or sub-section (3)] or`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 26, as the case may be, the Reserve Bank may impose on the person`
  line `contravening or committing default a penalty not exceeding ^3[ten lakh] rupees or twice the amount`
  line `involved in such contravention or default where such amount is quantifiable, whichever is more, and`
  line `where such contravention or default is a continuing one, a further penalty which may extend to twentyfive thousand rupees for every day after the first during which the contravention or default continues.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of imposing penalty under sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank shall serve a notice`
  line `on the defaulter requiring him to show cause why the amount specified in the notice should not be`
  line `imposed as a penalty and a reasonable opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such defaulter.`
  line
  line `(3) Any penalty imposed by the Reserve Bank under this section shall be payable within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date on which notice issued by the Reserve Bank demanding payment of the sum is`
  line `served on the defaulter and, in the event of failure of the person to pay the sum within such period, may`
  line `be recovered on a direction made by the principal civil court having jurisdiction in the area where the`
  line `registered office of the defaulter company or the official business of the person is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be made, except on an application made by an officer of the`
  line `Reserve Bank authorised by it in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The Reserve Bank may recover the amount of penalty by debiting the current account, if any, of`
  line `the defaulter or by liquidating the securities held to the credit of the defaulter or in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The court which makes a direction under sub-section (3) shall issue a certificate specifying the`
  line `sum payable by the defaulter and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as it were`
  line `a decree made by the court in a civil suit.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any complaint has been filed against any person in any court in respect of the`
  line `contravention or default of the nature referred to in sub-section (2), or, as the case may be, sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 26, then, no proceeding for the imposition of any penalty on the person shall be taken under`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 2 and schedule, ibid., for "fines" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2 and schedule, ibid., for "five lakh" (w.e.f. 22-1-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32499)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to compound offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32499&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act for any contravention, not being an`
  line `offence punishable with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine, may, on receipt of`
  line `an application from the person committing such contravention either before or after the institution of any`
  line `proceeding, be compounded by an officer of the Reserve Bank duly authorised by it in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a contravention has been compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further`
  line `proceeding, as the case may be, shall be initiated or continued, as the case may be, against the person`
  line `committing such contravention under that section, in respect of the contravention so compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32500)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32500&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32501)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Mode of recovery of penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929&sectionId=32501&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00005_200751_1517807326929
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The penalty imposed on the defaulter by the Reserve Bank`
  line `under section 30 may be recovered by issuing a notice to any person from whom any amount is due to the`
  line `defaulter, by requiring such person to deduct from the amount payable by him to the defaulter, the amount`
  line `payable to the Reserve Bank by way of penalty and pay to the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this section, every person to whom a notice is issued under this`
  line `sub-section shall be bound to comply with such notice, and, in particular, where such notice is issued to a`
  line `post office, bank or an insurer, it shall not be necessary for any passbook, deposit receipt, policy or any`
  line `other document to be produced for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like being made before`
  line `payment is made notwithstanding that any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary.`
  line
  line `(3) Any claim respecting any property in relation to which a notice under this sub-section has been`
  line `issued arising after the date of the notice shall be void as against any demand contained in the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a person to whom the notice under this sub-section is sent objects to it by a statement on`
  line `oath that the sum demanded or any part thereof is not due to the defaulter or that he does not hold any`
  line `money for or on account of the defaulter, then, nothing contained in this sub-section shall be deemed to`
  line `require such person to pay any such sum or part thereof, as the case may be, but if it is discovered that`
  line `such statement was false in any material particular, such person shall be personally liable to the Reserve`
  line `Bank to the extent of his own liability to the defaulter on the date of the notice, or to the extent of the`
  line `penalty imposed on the defaulter by the Reserve Bank, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(5) The Reserve Bank may at any time or from time to time, amend or revoke any notice issued under`
  line `this section or extend the time for making the payment in pursuance of such notice.`
  line
  line `(6) The Reserve Bank shall grant a receipt for any amount paid to it in compliance with a notice`
  line `issued under this section and the person so paying shall be fully discharged from his liability to the`
  line `defaulter to the extent of the amount so paid.`
  line
  line `(7) Any person discharging any liability to the defaulter after the receipt of a notice under this section`
  line `shall be personally liable to the Reserve Bank to the extent of his own liability to the defaulter so`
  line `discharged or to the extent of the penalty imposed on the defaulter by the Reserve Bank, whichever is`
  line less.
  line
  line `(8) If the person to whom the notice under this section is sent fails to make payment in pursuance`
  line `thereof to the Reserve Bank, he shall be deemed to be the defaulter in respect of the amount specified in`
  line `the notice and further proceedings may be taken against him for the realisation of the amount as if it were`
  line `an arrear due from him in the manner provided in this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "defaulter" means any person or system provider or`
  line `system participant on whom the Reserve Bank has imposed a penalty under section 30.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32502)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Act not to apply to stock exchanges or clearing corporations of stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
